<subSubSection lastPageId="39" lastPageNumber="40" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,334,585,611]" box="[189,334,585,611]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,585,611]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,585,611]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,455,632,694]" box="[234,325,632,658]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,325,632,658]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,455,632,694]" box="[189,455,667,694]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
BODY LENGTH. 
<quantity box="[357,450,667,694]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1399,733,900]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
HEAD. Head slightly wider than long. Integument black, except part of mandibles dark reddish-brown. Face sparsely covered with long, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[841,953,768,794]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1932,1958]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,558,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[189,1399,558,1888]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 19. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860634/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 19C</figureCitation>
). Clypeus almost flat with dispersed large, shallow punctation (i = 1–2 d); surface between punctures apically smooth or only superficially sculptured, shiny, basally more heavily sculptured and matt (
<figureCitation box="[902,985,838,864]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1932,1958]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,558,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[189,1399,558,1888]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 19. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860634/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
C–D). Malar area medially narrow, almost linear. Antenna dorsally blackish-brown, ventrally yellowish-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1399,939,1106]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
MESOSOMA. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc between punctures strongly reticulate, matt; disc sparsely (i = 2–3 d), finely and shallowly punctate (
<figureCitation box="[724,835,974,1000]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1932,1958]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,558,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[189,1399,558,1888]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 19. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860634/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 19B</figureCitation>
). Metanotum about half as long as basal area of propodeum, apically with distinct, narrow carinate depression (
<figureCitation box="[975,1084,1009,1035]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1932,1958]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,558,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[189,1399,558,1888]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 19. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860634/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 19B</figureCitation>
). Propodeum with distinct carination covering more than half of the basal area (
<figureCitation box="[829,938,1044,1071]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1932,1958]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,558,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[189,1399,558,1888]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 19. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860634/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 19B</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum sparsely covered with short, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[1128,1238,1080,1106]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1932,1958]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,558,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[189,1399,558,1888]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 19. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860634/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 19A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,888,1145,1172]" box="[189,888,1145,1172]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">WINGS. Yellowish-brown; wing venation and stigma brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1398,1211,1272]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">LEGS. Integument black to dark reddish-brown; fore tibia basally with small yellow spot. Vestiture greyish-white, scopa greyish-white, dorsally blackish-brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1399,1311,1479]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
METASOMA. Integument black, apical margins of terga sometimes narrowly translucent dark reddishbrown (
<figureCitation box="[278,383,1346,1373]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1932,1958]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,558,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[189,1399,558,1888]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 19. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860634/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 19E</figureCitation>
). Discs of T1 and T2 without hair; following terga with sparse and short but increasingly more and longer hair; apical tergal hair bands missing on all terga (
<figureCitation box="[981,1088,1382,1408]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1932,1958]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,558,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[189,1399,558,1888]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 19. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860634/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 19E</figureCitation>
). Prepygidial and pygidial fimbriae very sparse, brownish. Terga impunctate, superficially and ± densely sculptured, mostly shiny; T2–T4 with finely sculptured, narrow and indistinct apical tergal depression (
<figureCitation box="[1096,1202,1452,1478]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1932,1958]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,558,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[189,1399,558,1888]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 19. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860634/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 19E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,455,1518,1579]" box="[234,298,1518,1544]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,1518,1544]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,455,1518,1579]" box="[189,455,1553,1579]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
BODY LENGTH. 
<quantity box="[357,450,1553,1579]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="4.4">4.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1399,1618,1715]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
HEAD. Head slightly wider than long. Integument black, except mandible partly dark reddish-brown. Face densely covered with long, greyish-white, erect hair. Malar area medially narrow, almost linear. Antenna dorsally dark brown, ventrally dark orange-brown (
<figureCitation box="[898,1008,1688,1715]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,231,1900,1926]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[189,1399,522,1855]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 20. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860636/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1399,1754,1850]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
MESOSOMA. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc impunctate, strongly sculptured and matt. Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum sparsely covered with long, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[198,307,1824,1850]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,231,1900,1926]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[189,1399,522,1855]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 20. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860636/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,986,1890,1916]" box="[189,986,1890,1916]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">WINGS. Slightly yellowish-brown; wing venation and stigma brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1399,1955,2017]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
LEGS. Integument black to dark reddish-brown; fore tibia anteriorly dominantly yellow to yellowishbrown (
<figureCitation box="[280,390,1990,2017]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,231,1900,1926]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[189,1399,522,1855]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 20. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860636/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia unmodified. Vestiture greyish-white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[189,1399,267,400]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
METASOMA. Integument black, apical margins of terga partly translucent yellowish to dark reddishbrown (
<figureCitation box="[283,395,302,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,231,1900,1926]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[189,1399,522,1855]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 20. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860636/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 20C</figureCitation>
). Disc of T1 without hair; apical tergal hair bands missing on all terga (
<figureCitation box="[1274,1386,302,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,231,1900,1926]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[189,1399,522,1855]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 20. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860636/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 20C</figureCitation>
). Terga impunctate, sculptured and slightly matt; terga with broad and superficially sculptured, more shiny apical tergal depression (
<figureCitation box="[552,661,373,399]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,231,1900,1926]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[189,1399,522,1855]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 20. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860636/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 20C</figureCitation>
). S3–S5 without distinct apical hair fringes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[189,1332,438,465]" box="[189,1332,438,465]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
TERMINALIA. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[460,568,438,464]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,231,1900,1926]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[189,1399,522,1855]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 20. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860636/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 20B</figureCitation>
), S7 (
<figureCitation box="[636,743,438,464]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,231,1900,1926]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[189,1399,522,1855]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 20. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860636/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 20D</figureCitation>
) and terminal plate of S8 (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1160,438,464]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,231,1900,1926]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[189,1399,522,1855]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 20. Scrapter nigritarsis sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860636/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 20E</figureCitation>
) as illustrated.
</paragraph>
